-- PKO Bank, Tauron, KGHM May Move: Central European Equity Market Preview
-- Dorota Bartyzel
-- 2010-07-05T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/pko-bank-tauron-kghm-may-move-central-european-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  
 Poland’s  WIG20 Index  gained 1.3 percent, the Czech  PX Index 
climbed 1.7 percent and Hungary’s  BUX Index  added 1.4 percent.  
 PKO Bank Polski SA  (PKO PW): Poland’s biggest bank sold 600
million zloty ($181 million) of bad retail loans to investment
fund Best, Rzeczpospolita  reported  on July 3, citing Jan
Lisicki, head of the bank’s debt restructuring department. PKO
shares increased 1.5 percent to 36.7 zloty.  
 Tauron Polska Energia SA  (TPE PW): Polish copper producer
KGHM Polska Miedz SA raised its stake in the state-controlled
power utility to 5.2 percent from 4.9 percent, Tauron said in a
regulatory statement. Tauron added 0.2 percent to 5.06 zloty and
KGHM jumped 2.8 percent to 91 zloty.  
